<subSubSection id="C31428808561145BE796FEF3FD4C0693" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB17B0B8561145BE796FEF3FD4C0693" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198561145BE796FEF3FEEA06EE" bold="true" box="[199,308,368,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Remarks</emphasis>
. Resurrected genus, formerly considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888561145BE37CFEF2FA8706EE" authority="Kottelat, 2013" authorityName="Kottelat" authorityYear="2013" box="[1069,1369,367,392]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198561145BE37CFEF2FB5106EE" box="[1069,1167,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Dasyatis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F06FA8561145BE3F4FEECFA8F06EE" author="Kottelat" box="[1189,1361,367,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" refString="Kottelat, M. (2013) The fishes of the inland waters of southeast Asia: a catalogue and core bibliography of the fishes known to occur in freshwaters, mangroves and estuaries. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 27, 1 - 663." type="journal article" year="2013">Kottelat, 2013</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, now provisionally consists of eight somewhat morphologically heterogeneous species. Six of these species cluster together based on molecular data (see 
<figureCitation id="1335678E8561145BE514FE34FD5B06B6" box="[581,645,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dasyatidae (subfamily Dasyatinae). Topology and branch lengths resulting from a constrained Maximum Likelihood analysis of aligned NADH 2 sequence data using the GTR + I + G model. Topological constraints were derived from an unpublished ML analysis of whole mitochondrial genomes for a representative subset of the taxa (unpublished). Members of the Neotrygoninae were used as outgroups. Names shown at branch tips are those currently in use. Revised generic names proposed are shown to the right." pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), but provisional placement of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888561145BE4B7FE3AFBAA06B6" box="[998,1140,441,464]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Hypanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marianae">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198561145BE4B7FE3AFBAA06B6" box="[998,1140,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">H. marianae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888561145BE3FAFE3AFAD806B6" box="[1195,1286,439,464]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Hypanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rudis">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198561145BE3FAFE3AFAD806B6" box="[1195,1286,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">H. rudis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still needs to be confirmed when tissues become available.
</paragraph>
